A tragic collapse of a bridge in Minneapolis resulted in at least six deaths and numerous vehicles falling into the river.
Officials ruled out terrorism as the cause, attributing it to engineering issues.
Rescue efforts were underway, with reports of a school bus narrowly avoiding the disaster.
The incident prompted nationwide bridge inspections, with a focus on similar designs.
The community mourned the loss as investigations began to piece together the events leading to the catastrophic collapse.
Governor Tim Pawlenty ordered immediate inspections to prevent future tragedies, emphasizing the importance of infrastructure safety.
